messages.content: ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example is a simple implementation of the Paint-by-Example model based on its Hugging Face pipeline, designed to be used as a custom node in ComfyUI.
To install ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example, copy the repo and place it in the './custom_nodes' directory of your ComfyUI workplace. Then, install the required packages mentioned in the nodes.py file.
Is there a demo available for ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example?
Yes, there is a demo available that showcases the usage of the ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example node in a ComfyUI workspace. The demo can be found in the repo as 'demo.png'.
What is the purpose of ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example?

The purpose of ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example is to provide a simple implementation of the Paint-by-Example model that can be easily integrated into ComfyUI as a custom node, allowing users to generate images using the Paint-by-Example model within the ComfyUI environment.
Which repository is ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example based on?
ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example is based on the Paint-by-Example repository located at https://github.com/Fantasy-Studio/Paint-by-Example.
What is the Hugging Face pipeline used in ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example?
The Hugging Face pipeline used in ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example is the Paint-by-Example pipeline, which can be found at https://huggingface.co/Fantasy-Studio/Paint-by-Example.
Where should I place the ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example repo after copying it?
After copying the ComfyUI-Paint-by-Example repo, you should place it in the './custom_nodes' directory of your ComfyUI workplace.
